    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-26T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8287</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-26T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 27, 2.23 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2950. Referring to my despatch 5410, May 4,<note n="3" xml:id="d137fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_817">p. 817</ref>.</note> and
                    subsequent communications relative to the desire of the French Government that
                    the American Government be represented on the Permanent International Committee
                    of Economic Action, the Minister of Blockade now writes me saying that following
                    the recent conference held at Paris, the American Government had decided to send
                    a special delegate to the International Committee on Contingents, and Minister
                        <pb facs="0253" n="1007" xml:id="pg_1007"/> requests me to urge that the
                    American Government should also name on the same footing, delegates to the
                    International Committee of Economic Action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
